		<td><b>The Wrestler's &quot;Wrestle Jam&quot; NES game</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was recently convinced to watch this movie starring Mickey Rourke because my friend told me that it featured a fictional 8-bit Nintendo game. Sure enough, the game in it appeared to be pretty authentic, or a well-made hack of an existing NES game. So I checked the credits and it appears that a guy named Randall Furino was credited in it for "video game programming". Has anyone heard of this guy or any other project he's been involved in? And does anyone recognize which game was hacked into Wrestle Jam?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


